HEADWORD: Roisterer
<hw>Roist"er*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A blustering,
turbulent fellow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If two <qex>roisterers</qex> met, they cocked their hats in each
other faces.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roisterly</ent>⟦br⟧
